-- Merrill Lynch mulling Pagine Gialle buy: report
-- 
-- Sat Jul 28, 2007 4:58am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/07/28/us-merrill-paginegialle-idUSL2860214720070728

 

 MILAN  (Reuters) - Merrill Lynch MER.N is considering buying Italian yellow pages publisher Seat Pagine Gialle PG.MI, Italian daily Il Sole 24 Ore reported on Saturday citing financial sources. 

 Merrill has already conducted a due diligence study of the company, the newspaper said. Lehman Brothers is advising Seat's main shareholders - a group of funds including Cvc, Bc Partners, Investitori Associati and Permira, which hold a combined 49.6 percent of the shares - the paper said. Merrill Lynch and Seat Pagine Gialle were not immediately available for comment.